    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7c21d2e1_c55570f2",
        "filename": "android/emulation/control/ApkInstaller.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 190,
      "author": {
        "id": 1079203
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-03-23T22:43:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The reset() below tries to destroy a thread while its running.\n\nIn this case, mResultCallback blocks because the user is showed a modal dialog (we call dialog-\u003eexec() because -\u003eshow() crashed QEMU1). The modal dialog does prevent actions like screenshot, BUT, it doesn\u0027t prevent another drag-and-drop form happening.\n\nSo the problem here is twofold:\n1. Another drag-and-drop shouldn\u0027t be possible while a modal dialog is displayed. I will find a solution that prevents this from happening, and this crash will go away..\n2. For the general paradigm we follow here, if mResultCallback blocks (which it will when there are error messages) or just takes a long time in general AND it is possible to start() this object again, you can crash. One solution would be \"well, don\u0027t let mResultCallback block\", but that doesn\u0027t seem like a good solution.",
      "parentUuid": "7c21d2e1_0504a863",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 190,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 190,
        "endChar": 44
      },
      "revId": "145cbd5e399de925629866de4850e00f790280d2",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7c21d2e1_e5c07469",
        "filename": "android/emulation/control/ApkInstaller.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 190,
      "author": {
        "id": 1079203
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-03-23T23:02:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We may not fix this problem in ParallelTask, but it is a problem in the pattern we are using here.\n\nOnce you are in the scope of taskDoneFunction, parallelTask-\u003einFlight() is false. Therefore, if the result callback either blocks OR just takes a long time, its possible for the user to start up parallelTask again. And if, while that task is running, the result callback completes, we crash.",
      "parentUuid": "7c21d2e1_c55570f2",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 190,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 190,
        "endChar": 44
      },
      "revId": "145cbd5e399de925629866de4850e00f790280d2",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
